Step 1: Log in to Azure Portal
Sign in to your Azure Portal account.

Step 2: Create a Docker Container
Search for "Container Instances," click "Create," choose an image (like Apache or Nginx), and open port 80.

Step 3: Access Your Web Server
Go to your containerâ€™s page, copy its IP, and paste it in your browser.

Step 4: Customize the Web Server (Optional)
Connect to the container and install or configure your web server.

Step 5: Verify and Test Your Setup
Open the IP in your browser to check if the web server is working.
